Description: Implements Bayesian Lasso regression using efficient Gibbs
        sampling algorithms, including modified versions of the Hans
        and Park–Casella (PC) samplers. Includes functions for working
        with the Lasso distribution, such as its density, cumulative
        distribution, quantile, and random generation functions, along
        with moment calculations. Also includes a function to compute
        the Mills ratio. Designed for sparse linear models and suitable
        for high-dimensional regression problems.
